title.narrative: OUTPUT 6.2 FINANCING AND URBAN/SUBNATIONAL PLANNING FOR CHILDREN

description.narrative: Output 6.2 (Financing and urban/subnational planning for children) The government has improved its capacity to formulate and implement effective plans for children with sufficient fiscal space at the national, subnational, and urban level, and to include children as a priority in their national and local planning, allocating public expenditure accordingly., which contributes to Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement, Reducing Child Poverty, Reducing Child Poverty (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Children and adolescents, especially the poorest and most vulnerable children, benefit from evidence based planning and public expenditure, reliable data and an expanded universal social protection system that accounts for environmental risks and disasters.

description.narrative: UNICEF supported the Government of Indonesia to develop an analytical framework and analyse national budgets focusing on health, education, child protection and social protection to advance public finance for children. It drew government attention to the issues of inclusive recovery from COVID-19 under the Finance Track of the G20 Presidency, implementing the Joint SDG Fund on Innovative Financing to accelerate investment in SDGs, completing the Situation Analysis on Children and Young People in Cities, and developing the first-ever Subnational COVID-19 Recovery Plan for Children together with the government of Central Java Province. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:10/12/2021
